The men are believed to have stolen a silver Mercedes Benz and kidnapped the passengers earlier this month. JOHANNESBURG Police have today arrested six people for hijacking, kidnapping and the rape of a 16-year-old in Soweto. The men are believed to have stolen a silver Mercedes Benz and kidnapped the passengers earlier this month.Police are however searching for four other men who fled the scene Johannebsurg Metro Police Department s Wayne Minaar says, Officers from the JMPD K-9 unit arrested six suspects when they found them with a Mercedes Benz when they were busy changing the number plates. It was discovered that the Mercedes Benz was hijacked on 27 December. Two males and a female were taken hostage. 